defs.docs:
The `csv` crate provides a fast and flexible CSV reader and writer, with
support for Serde.

defs.name: ByteRecord
defs.docs: A single CSV record stored as raw bytes.

defs.docs: Create a new empty `ByteRecord`.

defs.name: as_slice
defs.docs:
Return the entire row as a single byte slice. The slice returned stores

defs.name: Position
defs.docs: A position in CSV data.

defs.docs: Returns a new position initialized to the start value.

defs.name: byte
defs.docs: The byte offset, starting at `0`, of this position.

defs.name: line
defs.docs: The line number, starting at `1`, of this position.

defs.docs: Set the record index of this position.

defs.name: ByteRecordIter
defs.docs: A double-ended iterator over the fields in a byte record.

defs.name: cookbook
defs.docs: A cookbook of examples for CSV reading and writing.

defs.name: DeserializeError
defs.docs: An Serde deserialization error.

defs.name: Message
defs.docs: A generic Serde deserialization error.

defs.name: Unsupported
defs.docs: A generic Serde unsupported error.

defs.name: UnexpectedEndOfRow
defs.docs:
This error occurs when a Rust type expects to decode another field
 from a row, but no more fields exist.

defs.name: InvalidUtf8
defs.docs:
This error occurs when UTF-8 validation on a field fails. UTF-8
 validation is only performed when the Rust type requires it (e.g.,
 a `String` or `&str` type).

defs.name: ParseBool
defs.docs: This error occurs when a boolean value fails to parse.

defs.name: ParseInt
defs.docs: This error occurs when an integer value fails to parse.

defs.name: ParseFloat
defs.docs: This error occurs when a float value fails to parse.

defs.name: DeserializeErrorKind
defs.value: DeserializeErrorKind::{Message, Unsupported, UnexpectedEndOfRow, InvalidUtf8, ParseBool, ParseInt, ParseFloat}
defs.docs: The type of a Serde deserialization error.

defs.name: field
defs.docs: Return the field index (starting at 0) of this error, if available.

defs.name: kind
defs.docs: Return the underlying error kind.

defs.name: Result
defs.docs: A type alias for `Result<T, csv::Error>`.

defs.name: Error
defs.docs: An error that can occur when processing CSV data.

defs.name: kind
defs.docs: Return the specific type of this error.

defs.name: into_kind
defs.docs: Unwrap this error into its underlying type.

defs.name: is_io_error
defs.docs: Returns true if this is an I/O error.

defs.name: position
defs.docs: Return the position for this error, if one exists.

defs.name: Io
defs.docs: An I/O error that occurred while reading CSV data.

defs.name: Utf8
defs.docs:
A UTF-8 decoding error that occured while reading CSV data into Rust
 `String`s.

defs.name: UnequalLengths
defs.docs:
This error occurs when two records with an unequal number of fields
 are found. This error only occurs when the `flexible` option in a
 CSV reader/writer is disabled.

defs.name: Seek
defs.docs:
This error occurs when either the `byte_headers` or `headers` methods
 are called on a CSV reader that was asked to `seek` before it parsed
 the first record.

defs.name: Serialize
defs.docs: An error of this kind occurs only when using the Serde serializer.

defs.name: Deserialize
defs.docs:
An error of this kind occurs only when performing automatic
 deserialization with serde.

defs.name: __Nonexhaustive
defs.docs: Hints that destructuring should not be exhaustive.

defs.name: ErrorKind
defs.value: ErrorKind::{Io, Utf8, UnequalLengths, Seek, Serialize, Deserialize, __Nonexhaustive}
defs.docs: The specific type of an error.

defs.name: position
defs.docs: Return the position for this error, if one exists.

defs.name: FromUtf8Error
defs.docs: A UTF-8 validation error during record conversion.

defs.name: into_byte_record
defs.docs: Access the underlying `ByteRecord` that failed UTF-8 validation.

defs.name: utf8_error
defs.docs: Access the underlying UTF-8 validation error.

defs.name: Utf8Error
defs.docs: A UTF-8 validation error.

defs.name: field
defs.docs: The field index of a byte record in which UTF-8 validation failed.

defs.name: valid_up_to
defs.docs: The index into the given field up to which valid UTF-8 was verified.

defs.name: IntoInnerError
defs.docs: `IntoInnerError` occurs when consuming a `Writer` fails.

defs.name: error
defs.docs: Returns the error which caused the call to `into_inner` to fail.

defs.name: into_inner
defs.docs: Returns the underlying writer which generated the error.

defs.name: Always
defs.docs: This puts quotes around every field. Always.

defs.name: Necessary
defs.docs: This puts quotes around fields only when necessary.

defs.name: NonNumeric
defs.docs:
This puts quotes around all fields that are non-numeric. Namely, when
 writing a field that does not parse as a valid float or integer, then
 quotes will be used even if they aren't strictly necessary.

defs.name: Never
defs.docs: This *never* writes quotes, even if it would produce invalid CSV data.
